history.content:
Please see the opportunity below. 
***********

We still have spots available for students who are interested in volunteering at the Structure Security Conference on September 27 & 28. By completing one 6-hour shift, students can mingle and enjoy the rest of the conference days for free. 


Details are below and sign-up information is included below.

===========================================

Structure Security 2016

http://www.structuresecurity.com/

===========================================


DATES

Wednesday, September 27, 2016 - 7:30am - 6:00pm

Thursday, September 28, 2016 - 7:30am - 6:00pm


LOCATION

Golden Gate Club

135 Fisher Loop, San Francisco, CA 94129


VOLUNTEER RULES:
As a volunteer you are welcome to attend the entire event and the reception.  All we ask is that you attend ONE of the mandatory volunteer calls on Wednesday, September 21st (see below), report to your shift on time and perform your assigned tasks during your shift.  Dress code is business casual.


======================================

MANDATORY PRE-PLANNING CALL

======================================

Please plan to join a short pre-planning call so that we can review details, assign positions and answer any questions.


Option 1: Wednesday, September 21 - 9:30am PT

Option 2: Wednesday, September 21 - 1:00pm PT


Dial-In: (530) 881-1212
Passcode: 894-578-320


SHIFTS

Tuesday, September 27

8:00am - 1:00pm – (arrive 7:30am)   

1:00pm - 6:00pm – (arrive 12:30pm)      


Wednesday, September 28

8:00am - 1:00pm – (arrive 7:30am)   

1:00pm - 6:00pm – (arrive 12:30pm)         


HOW TO SIGN UP

Enter your name, email, and cell number into this Google Doc:http://bit.ly/29DPAVy


DRESS:

Business casual, no jeans, wear comfy shoes, no sneakers

Men – slacks and a polo or collared shirt

Women – slacks, dress, we suggest staying away from high heels, as there will be a lot of standing and/or walking


Please let me know if you have any questions!


Thanks,

Liz
history.subject: Opportunity: ISO Volunteers for the Structure Security Conference, 9/27 & 9/28
